    "body": "This is a bit tricky. The same error is actually sensible if there **is** an outer loop:\n\n``` rust\nfn main() { loop { let x = { break }; } }\n```\n\nBut if `rustc` is to report error eagerly, it is quite the same as:\n\n``` rust\nfn main() { let x = { break }; }\n```\n",
